## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="3904e-197">Une recherche asynchrone peut afficher les résultats qu’ils sont trouvent tout en poursuivant la recherche de résultats supplémentaires.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3904e-197">An asynchronous search can show results as they are found while simultaneously searching for additional results.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="3904e-198">Cela est utile pour les tâches comme le remplissage des zones de liste.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3904e-198">This is useful for tasks such as populating list boxes.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="3904e-199">Le paramètre par défaut de cette propriété est `false`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3904e-199">The default setting for this property is `false`.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="3904e-200">L’exemple c# suivant montre comment créer une recherche asynchrone.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3904e-200">The following C# example shows how to create an asynchronous search.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
using System.DirectoryServices;  
...  
// Bind to the users container.  
DirectoryEntry entry = new DirectoryEntry("LDAP://CN=users,DC=fabrikam,DC=com");  
// Create a DirectorySearcher object.  
DirectorySearcher mySearcher = new DirectorySearcher(entry);  
//Set the Asynchronous property to true.  
src.Asynchronous = true;  
//Use the FindAll method to get search results.  
SearchResultCollection res = src.FindAll();  
  
```

  
  
## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="3904e-204">L’attribut a la valeur de cette propriété doit être un attribut de nom unique, tels que le membre ou managedBy.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3904e-204">The attribute that this property is set to must be a distinguished name attribute, such as member or managedBy.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="3904e-205">L’attribut peut être unique ou à valeurs multiples.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3904e-205">The attribute can be either single or multi-valued.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="3904e-206">Pour plus d’informations, consultez le [membre](/windows/desktop/adschema/a-member) et [Managed By](/windows/desktop/adschema/a-managedby) articles.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3904e-206">For more information, see the [Member](/windows/desktop/adschema/a-member) and [Managed-By](/windows/desktop/adschema/a-managedby) articles.</span></span>
  
 <span data-ttu-id="3904e-207">La recherche est effectuée sur les objets qui sont identifiés par le nom unique qui est spécifié dans l’attribut de l’objet de base.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3904e-207">The search is performed against the objects that are identified by the distinguished name that is specified in the attribute of the base object.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="3904e-208">Par exemple, si l’objet de base est une classe de groupe adschema et <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectorySearcher.AttributeScopeQuery%2A> est définie sur « membre », la recherche sera effectuée par rapport à tous les objets qui sont membres du groupe.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3904e-208">For example, if the base object is an adschema group class and the <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectorySearcher.AttributeScopeQuery%2A> is set to "member," then the search will be performed against all objects that are members of the group.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="3904e-209">Pour plus d’informations, consultez le [groupe classe](/windows/desktop/adschema/c-group) article.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3904e-209">For more information, see the [Group class](/windows/desktop/adschema/c-group) article.</span></span>
  
 <span data-ttu-id="3904e-210">Lorsque le <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectorySearcher.AttributeScopeQuery%2A> propriété est utilisée, le <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectorySearcher.SearchScope%2A> propriété doit être définie sur <xref:System.DirectoryServices.SearchScope.Base>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3904e-210">When the <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectorySearcher.AttributeScopeQuery%2A> property is used, the <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectorySearcher.SearchScope%2A> property must be set to <xref:System.DirectoryServices.SearchScope.Base>.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="3904e-211">Si le <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectorySearcher.SearchScope%2A> propriété est définie sur une autre valeur, en définissant le <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectorySearcher.AttributeScopeQuery%2A> propriété lèvera une <xref:System.ArgumentException>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3904e-211">If the <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectorySearcher.SearchScope%2A> property is set to any other value, setting the <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectorySearcher.AttributeScopeQuery%2A> property will throw an <xref:System.ArgumentException>.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="3904e-212">Pour plus d’informations, consultez le [exécution d’une requête de portée d’attribut](/windows/desktop/adsi/performing-an-attribute-scoped-query).</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3904e-212">For more information, see the [Performing an Attribute Scope Query](/windows/desktop/adsi/performing-an-attribute-scoped-query).</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="3904e-213">L’exemple suivant montre comment utiliser le <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectorySearcher.AttributeScopeQuery%2A> propriété avec l’attribut de membre pour obtenir les membres d’un groupe.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3904e-213">The following example shows how to use the <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectorySearcher.AttributeScopeQuery%2A> property with the member attribute to get the members of a group.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="3904e-214">Il imprime ensuite le premier et le nom des membres et leurs numéros de téléphone.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3904e-214">It then prints out the first and last names of the members and their telephone numbers.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
using System.DirectoryServices;  
DirectoryEntry group = new DirectoryEntry("LDAP://CN=MyGroup, …");  
DirectorySearcher src = new DirectorySearcher(group "(&(objectClass=user)(objectCategory=Person))");  
src.AttributeScopedQuery = "member";  
src.PropertiesToLoad.Add("sn");  
src.PropertiesToLoad.Add("givenName");  
src.PropertiesToLoad.Add("telephoneNumber");  
foreach(SearchResult res in src.FindAll())  
{  
    Console.WriteLine("…");  
}  
```

  
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="3904e-232">L’exemple c# suivant montre comment définir le <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectorySearcher.DerefAlias%2A> propriété <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DereferenceAlias.Always> , afin qu’elle déréférence les alias lors de la recherche des subordonnées et la localisation des objets de base.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3904e-232">The following C# example shows how to set the <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectorySearcher.DerefAlias%2A> property to <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DereferenceAlias.Always> , so that it dereferences aliases when both searching subordinates and locating base objects.</span></span>  
  
```  
using System.DirectoryServices;  
...  
// Bind to the users container.  
DirectoryEntry entry = new DirectoryEntry("LDAP://CN=users,DC=fabrikam,DC=com");  
// Create a DirectorySearcher object.  
DirectorySearcher mySearcher = new DirectorySearcher(entry);  
// Set DerefAlias to Always.  
src.DerefAlias = DerefenceAlias.Always;  
//Use the FindAll method to get search results.  
SearchResultCollection res = src.FindAll();  
  
```

  
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="3904e-242">L’exemple suivant montre comment retourner une collection de noms uniques au format hexadécimal.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3904e-242">The following example shows how to return a collection of distinguished names in hexadecimal format.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
using System.DirectoryServices;  
...  
DirectorySearcher src = new DirectorySearcher("…");  
src.PropertiesToLoad = new string[] {ntSecurityDescriptor,…};  
src.ExtendedDN = ExtendedDN.HexString;  
SearchResultCollection res = src.FindAll();  
  
```

  
  
## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="3904e-303">Si <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectorySearcher.SearchRoot%2A> est une référence null (`Nothing` en Visual Basic), la racine de recherche est définie sur la racine du domaine que votre serveur utilise actuellement.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3904e-303">If <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectorySearcher.SearchRoot%2A> is a null reference (`Nothing` in Visual Basic), the search root is set to the root of the domain that your server is currently using.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="3904e-304">Il existe plusieurs façons de rechercher dans le catalogue global :</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3904e-304">There are several ways to search in the global catalog:</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="3904e-305">Énumérer le catalogue global et sélectionner le premier enfant.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3904e-305">Enumerate the global catalog and pick the first child.</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="3904e-306">Spécifiez le nom du serveur.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3904e-306">Specify the server name.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="3904e-307">Utilisez la fonction DsGetDcName pour rechercher le catalogue global.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3904e-307">Use the DsGetDcName function to find the global catalog.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="3904e-308">Pour plus d’informations sur la fonction DsGetDcName, consultez la [DsGetDcName](/windows/desktop/api/dsgetdc/nf-dsgetdc-dsgetdcnamea).</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3904e-308">For more information on the DsGetDcName function, see the [DsGetDcName](/windows/desktop/api/dsgetdc/nf-dsgetdc-dsgetdcnamea).</span></span>
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="3904e-309">Obtenir l’objet RootDSE du catalogue global et demandez « rootNamingContext ».</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3904e-309">Get the RootDSE  of the global catalog and ask for "rootNamingContext".</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="3904e-310">Utiliser le catalogue global, en spécifiant un chemin de recherche comme si à l’aide de LDAP.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3904e-310">Use the global catalog, specifying a search path as if using LDAP.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="3904e-311">Par exemple, « GC : / / unité d’organisation =..., DC =..., DC =... ».</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3904e-311">For example, "GC://OU=..., DC=..., DC=...".</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="3904e-312">Le code c# suivant montre comment énumérer le catalogue global et sélectionner le premier enfant.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3904e-312">The following C# code shows how to enumerate the global catalog and pick the first child.</span></span>  
  
    ```csharp  
    DirectoryEntry entry = new DirectoryEntry("GC://forestname");  
    IEnumerator ie = entry.Children.GetEnumerator();  
    ie.MoveNext();  
    entry = (DirectoryEntry)ie.Current;  
    DirectorySearcher search = new DirectorySearcher(entry);  
    ```

  
  
## Examples  
  
```csharp  
using System.DirectoryServices;  
...  
DirectorySearcher src = new DirectorySearcher("…");  
src.PropertiesToLoad = new string[] {ntSecurityDescriptor,…};  
src.SecurityMasks = SecurityMasks.Dacl | SecurityMasks.Owner;  
SearchResultCollection res = src.FindAll();  
  
```

  
  
